<h1>Problem 1971 - 2023 IMOSL, G5, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute-angled triangle with circumcircle \(\omega\) and circumcentre \(O\). Points \(D\neq B\) and \(E\neq C\) lie on \(\omega\) such that \(BD\perp AC\) and \(CE\perp AB\). Let \(CO\) meet \(AB\) at \(X\), and \(BO\) meet \(AC\) at \(Y\).</p>
<p>Prove that the circumcircles of triangles \(BXD\) and \(CYE\) have an intersection lie on line \(AO\).</p>
